# The Collection hierarchy

## `java.util`, one family tree

- `Iterable` → `Collection` → **`List`** · **`Set`** · **`Queue`/`Deque`**
- **`Map<K,V>`** sits alongside — key→value, not a plain element holder

## The four shapes

- **`List`** — ordered, indexed, **duplicates** ok
- **`Set`** — **no duplicates**
- **`Queue`/`Deque`** — FIFO / double-ended
- **`Map`** — key-to-value lookup
- Each has several implementations — the next sections are that choice
